This paper deals with coding schemes for a broadcast channel with secrecy constraints, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on the use of complementary receiver side information, which is a technique used in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of coding theory to achieve secrecy, which falls under the category of coding and information theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of satellite codewords, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) depending on the context.
